441
00:42:07,591 --> 00:42:09,393
Congratulations, dear.

442
00:42:09,460 --> 00:42:10,594
I'm sorry.

443
00:42:11,428 --> 00:42:12,630
I'm late.

444
00:42:13,664 --> 00:42:14,832
I'm proud of you, dear.

445
00:42:18,903 --> 00:42:20,838
UNIVERSITY OF THE CITY OF MANILA

446
00:42:21,539 --> 00:42:22,673
Thank you.

447
00:42:36,687 --> 00:42:37,888
Ms. Infantes.

448
00:42:48,766 --> 00:42:51,135
Mom. Dad.

449
00:42:51,201 --> 00:42:53,771
This is Mr. Torres.

450
00:42:53,837 --> 00:42:55,673
My Philippine Studies professor.

451
00:42:56,807 --> 00:43:00,411
I congratulate you on your daughter Klay.

452
00:43:00,477 --> 00:43:02,012
I'm so proud of this young woman.

453
00:43:03,614 --> 00:43:04,882
Thank you.

454
00:43:06,617 --> 00:43:07,918
Ah, right.

455
00:43:07,985 --> 00:43:11,322
I just dropped by to give
you your graduation gift.

456
00:43:11,388 --> 00:43:12,556
Oh!

457
00:43:12,623 --> 00:43:13,691
You don't have to, sir!

458
00:43:13,757 --> 00:43:15,225
Gosh!

459
00:43:15,292 --> 00:43:18,329
What's this?
I wonder where you got this from.

460
00:43:18,395 --> 00:43:19,496
Then open it.

461
00:43:32,843 --> 00:43:35,613
I found a scholarship program

462
00:43:35,679 --> 00:43:37,281
and I'm able to get you in.

463
00:43:38,015 --> 00:43:41,118
I sent them your records and,

464
00:43:41,185 --> 00:43:45,122
goodness, there were a lot
of recommendations from the school admin

465
00:43:45,189 --> 00:43:47,157
and from your other professors.

466
00:43:47,224 --> 00:43:48,425
So there!

467
00:43:49,927 --> 00:43:51,962
You'll be able to save money there

468
00:43:53,230 --> 00:43:55,065
and you can send some back to your family.

469
00:43:55,833 --> 00:43:59,503
And I hope you gain a lot of knowledge

470
00:44:00,137 --> 00:44:02,172
that you can bring to our country.

471
00:44:05,075 --> 00:44:06,276
I'm excited

472
00:44:07,044 --> 00:44:11,348
for you to continue healing
and treating this country.

473
00:44:12,449 --> 00:44:13,751
Future

474
00:44:13,817 --> 00:44:18,389
Dr. Maria Clara Infantes.

475
00:44:20,591 --> 00:44:21,959
Gosh, sir!

476
00:44:22,526 --> 00:44:25,396
You keep taking me everywhere.

477
00:44:27,131 --> 00:44:28,499
But…

478
00:44:28,565 --> 00:44:30,367
wherever I end up,

479
00:44:31,168 --> 00:44:33,437
I will always find my way back home.

480
00:44:34,104 --> 00:44:35,606
Good!

481
00:44:37,641 --> 00:44:39,843
Oh! Wow!

482
00:44:45,349 --> 00:44:51,889
UNIVERSITY OF THE CITY OF MANILA

483
00:44:55,559 --> 00:45:00,330
Do you mean that
reading <i>Noli</i> is useless?

484
00:45:00,397 --> 00:45:06,403
A book that significantly contributed
to easing the struggles of Filipinos.

485
00:45:07,538 --> 00:45:09,673
Submit a book report.

486
00:45:09,740 --> 00:45:11,508
And read this one.

487
00:45:12,509 --> 00:45:14,645
You will learn more from this version.

488
00:45:14,712 --> 00:45:16,480
And this book will take you

489
00:45:16,547 --> 00:45:18,615
to the world that Jose Rizal created.

490
00:45:18,682 --> 00:45:20,584
So that you can learn the whole history.

491
00:45:32,563 --> 00:45:33,764
There's an emergency.

492
00:45:37,267 --> 00:45:38,435
Which book?

493
00:45:38,502 --> 00:45:40,804
-<i>The Preying Birds</i>, sir.
-Well then.

494
00:45:41,371 --> 00:45:42,539
Are you with the others now?

495
00:45:45,909 --> 00:45:47,111
Assist me, okay?

496
00:45:47,177 --> 00:45:50,013
You will show yourselves
only to the characters.

497
00:45:51,081 --> 00:45:53,784
Gosh! I'm too old for
this kind of journey.

498
00:46:10,501 --> 00:46:13,370
Good thing his WBC has stabilized.

499
00:46:14,638 --> 00:46:15,539
All right.

500
00:46:15,606 --> 00:46:18,275
I'll just drop by here
then I'll be there for a second.

501
00:46:19,810 --> 00:46:20,878
All right.

502
00:46:21,779 --> 00:46:23,380
Thank you, girl!

503
00:46:42,833 --> 00:46:44,535
<i>That's why this country remains stagnant</i>

504
00:46:44,601 --> 00:46:47,237
because of Filipinos like you
who don't care about

505
00:46:47,304 --> 00:46:48,772
the true events in history!

506
00:46:50,908 --> 00:46:52,676
It's really hard to love the Philippines.

507
00:46:54,111 --> 00:46:57,481
And to be honest, I have no plans
of working here after I graduate.

508
00:46:58,015 --> 00:47:00,150
If I get a chance to leave,
I will never go back.

509
00:47:06,323 --> 00:47:08,992
And I hope you gain a lot of knowledge

510
00:47:09,059 --> 00:47:10,928
that you can bring back to our country.

511
00:47:10,994 --> 00:47:13,163
Wherever I end up,

512
00:47:13,864 --> 00:47:16,600
I will always find my way back home.

513
00:47:16,667 --> 00:47:18,001
Good!

514
00:47:54,838 --> 00:47:55,839
Yes?

515
00:47:55,906 --> 00:47:58,275
Would you know where
I could find Mr. Torres?

516
00:47:58,342 --> 00:48:00,344
The one who teaches Philippine Studies?

517
00:48:00,410 --> 00:48:03,247
Ah, Mr. Torres is gone.

518
00:48:04,915 --> 00:48:06,016
He's dead?

519
00:48:06,516 --> 00:48:08,552
No, he's not yet dead.

520
00:48:08,619 --> 00:48:12,022
What I meant was,
he's not with the university anymore.

521
00:48:12,589 --> 00:48:14,291
Ah, is that so?

522
00:48:15,292 --> 00:48:17,160
Too bad. I came here to see him.

523
00:48:17,227 --> 00:48:18,795
I have a surprise for him.

524
00:48:18,862 --> 00:48:20,530
I brought him a gift.

525
00:48:20,597 --> 00:48:24,134
If you want, you can just
give it to Sir Barry Torres.

526
00:48:24,201 --> 00:48:25,936
He's Mr. Torres's grandson.

527
00:48:27,271 --> 00:48:28,972
Barry Torres?

528
00:48:29,940 --> 00:48:31,275
All right. Where is he?

529
00:48:35,245 --> 00:48:36,613
That's Sir Barry.

530
00:48:37,114 --> 00:48:38,548
I'll leave you to it.

531
00:48:38,615 --> 00:48:39,516
Thank you.

532
00:48:40,884 --> 00:48:42,986
I want you to tell me

533
00:48:43,053 --> 00:48:45,822
why Dr. Jose Rizal wrote

534
00:48:45,889 --> 00:48:50,193
<i>Noli Me Tangere</i> and <i>El Filibusterismo.</i>

535
00:48:53,196 --> 00:48:55,065
I want you to write
a book report about it.

536
00:48:55,966 --> 00:48:57,567
Submit it to me next month, okay?

537
00:48:57,634 --> 00:48:59,002
-Okay, sir.
-Okay, sir.

538
00:49:11,281 --> 00:49:12,149
Ah, Mr. Torres!

539
00:49:12,215 --> 00:49:13,283
Mr. Barry To--

540
00:49:19,056 --> 00:49:20,090
Sir Ibarra?

541
00:49:31,168 --> 00:49:32,602
Are you my former student?

542
00:49:41,945 --> 00:49:44,214
My real name is Ibarra Gonzalo Torres.

543
00:49:44,281 --> 00:49:45,248
But…

544
00:49:45,849 --> 00:49:47,484
just call me Barry.

545
00:49:50,787 --> 00:49:52,422
And you are…

546
00:49:54,658 --> 00:49:56,393
Dr. Klay Infantes.

547
00:49:59,896 --> 00:50:02,532
Mr. Torres's former student.

548
00:50:02,599 --> 00:50:03,667
Your grandfather.

549
00:50:04,267 --> 00:50:06,303
Nice to meet you, Dr. Infantes.

550
00:50:07,337 --> 00:50:09,006
So, you used to be
my grandfather's student.

551
00:50:10,607 --> 00:50:11,808
Just call me Klay.

552
00:50:15,112 --> 00:50:16,380
Why are you here?

553
00:50:17,547 --> 00:50:18,548
Are you going to teach here?

554
00:50:19,549 --> 00:50:20,617
No.

555
00:50:20,684 --> 00:50:22,319
I came here to visit him.

556
00:50:22,386 --> 00:50:23,720
I brought him something.

557
00:50:27,657 --> 00:50:28,692
Okay.

558
00:50:29,559 --> 00:50:30,794
I'll just give it to him.

559
00:50:30,861 --> 00:50:31,828
But…

560
00:50:32,496 --> 00:50:33,730
he's busier than I am.

561
00:50:39,002 --> 00:50:40,270
That's so sad.

562
00:50:41,371 --> 00:50:43,640
So Mr. Torres doesn't
teach here at PLM anymore?

563
00:50:44,641 --> 00:50:47,144
But sometimes, he visits.

564
00:50:52,516 --> 00:50:53,717
Maria Clara?

565
00:50:56,353 --> 00:50:59,790
That's great. She's a <i>Noli</i>
and <i>El Fili</i> fan.

566
00:51:00,824 --> 00:51:02,959
By the way, Dr. Infantes, this is Clarize.

567
00:51:03,860 --> 00:51:05,695
She's a music teacher here and

568
00:51:05,762 --> 00:51:06,963
she's my wife.

569
00:51:07,631 --> 00:51:09,800
The soon-to-be mother of my child.

570
00:51:13,570 --> 00:51:15,505
Can I also teach there?

571
00:51:15,572 --> 00:51:16,673
Just like the…

572
00:51:17,207 --> 00:51:19,342
the nuns at the convent.

573
00:51:19,409 --> 00:51:20,644
That even taught us,

574
00:51:21,878 --> 00:51:22,813
music.

575
00:51:24,147 --> 00:51:26,216
Clarize, this is Dr. Infantes.

576
00:51:27,451 --> 00:51:29,319
Grandpa's former student.

577
00:51:29,386 --> 00:51:30,787
Oh.

578
00:51:32,055 --> 00:51:33,623
Nice to meet you, doctor.

579
00:51:57,380 --> 00:51:59,950
You remind me of my best friend.

580
00:52:08,158 --> 00:52:10,427
They finally got their happy ending.

581
00:52:18,902 --> 00:52:20,237
For your career,

582
00:52:21,438 --> 00:52:22,839
for the two of you,

583
00:52:24,641 --> 00:52:25,809
for your baby.

584
00:52:37,621 --> 00:52:38,522
You can count on that.

585
00:52:38,588 --> 00:52:40,323
I'll always visit here.

586
00:52:44,828 --> 00:52:45,962
Sorry.

587
00:52:46,029 --> 00:52:47,998
Can I hug you both again

588
00:52:48,064 --> 00:52:49,566
but this time with consent?

589
00:53:16,459 --> 00:53:18,061
Well then, Dr. Infantes.

590
00:53:18,128 --> 00:53:20,063
We still have a faculty meeting to attend.

591
00:53:20,130 --> 00:53:21,565
And we might be late.

592
00:53:21,631 --> 00:53:23,500
I'll just give it to grandpa.

593
00:53:23,567 --> 00:53:25,635
And tell him that you visited here.

594
00:53:26,136 --> 00:53:27,837
Okay, thank you. You two take care.

595
00:53:32,042 --> 00:53:32,943
Until then.

596
00:53:33,944 --> 00:53:35,011
You can count on it.

597
00:53:36,112 --> 00:53:37,714
Okay. You two take care.

598
00:53:37,781 --> 00:53:39,583
Let's go. We might be late.

599
00:53:57,234 --> 00:53:59,302
<i>I love you very much.</i>

600
00:54:00,370 --> 00:54:01,838
<i>I love you very much too…</i>

601
00:54:03,773 --> 00:54:04,941
My Ms. Klay.

602
00:54:31,301 --> 00:54:33,136
Is there anything new written on it?

603
00:54:35,639 --> 00:54:37,140
None.

604
00:54:37,207 --> 00:54:38,575
There's nothing new written here.

605
00:54:58,328 --> 00:54:59,763
You don't have a fever.

606
00:55:02,766 --> 00:55:05,869
But you looked pale and weak all along.

607
00:55:09,139 --> 00:55:10,340
Is it because of your wound--

608
00:55:10,407 --> 00:55:12,342
It's just a bullet graze wound, Ms. Klay.

609
00:55:15,312 --> 00:55:16,446
You know what?

610
00:55:17,480 --> 00:55:20,383
Maybe your body is taking revenge on you.

611
00:55:20,450 --> 00:55:24,654
You must rest from
time to time to regain your strength.

612
00:55:25,822 --> 00:55:27,691
These vegetables will soon be cooked.

613
00:55:28,925 --> 00:55:31,861
You need nourishment
so you'll gain strength

614
00:55:31,928 --> 00:55:33,730
because this fight
still has a long way to go.

615
00:55:34,731 --> 00:55:35,832
It seems like…

616
00:55:36,566 --> 00:55:38,401
I am feeling much better.

617
00:55:41,071 --> 00:55:43,606
Now that I am looking at you,

618
00:55:44,607 --> 00:55:45,475
I feel like

619
00:55:46,876 --> 00:55:49,879
my beloved wife is cooking for me.

620
00:55:52,882 --> 00:55:54,117
What wife?

621
00:55:54,684 --> 00:55:55,919
I could be like a mother too.

622
00:56:23,012 --> 00:56:24,381
There you go.

623
00:56:24,948 --> 00:56:26,483
Let me taste the food…

624
00:56:27,317 --> 00:56:28,485
that my wife cooked for me.

625
00:56:36,760 --> 00:56:38,495
Is it good?

626
00:56:38,561 --> 00:56:39,829
Extraordinary!

627
00:56:42,265 --> 00:56:44,067
You're indeed my wife, Ms. Klay!

628
00:56:46,236 --> 00:56:51,207
It's my first time tasting this kind

629
00:56:51,274 --> 00:56:52,609
of sauteed vegetables.

630
00:56:53,209 --> 00:56:57,480
My spirit was indeed lifted
because of your sumptuous love.

631
00:56:57,547 --> 00:56:58,415
It's your turn.

632
00:56:59,783 --> 00:57:00,884
Say ah.

633
00:57:11,094 --> 00:57:13,263
How about him? Will I ever see him again?

634
00:57:17,934 --> 00:57:19,769
In whatever version,

635
00:57:20,670 --> 00:57:22,405
in whatever way…

636
00:57:26,042 --> 00:57:28,011
even in a dream again…

637
00:57:30,447 --> 00:57:32,348
I hope we meet again.

638
00:57:35,985 --> 00:57:36,953
Multiverse,

639
00:57:37,020 --> 00:57:38,721
give me some crumbs of Fidel.

640
00:57:49,132 --> 00:57:51,434
But of course, life goes on.

641
00:57:53,603 --> 00:57:55,038
The fight is still on.

642
00:58:05,849 --> 00:58:07,283
How are you, sir?

643
00:58:07,350 --> 00:58:08,551
I'm all right.

644
00:58:09,385 --> 00:58:10,753
Are you eating well?

645
00:58:10,820 --> 00:58:12,188
Yes, he is, doctor.

646
00:58:13,523 --> 00:58:15,158
Let's check it again, okay?

647
00:58:15,825 --> 00:58:18,895
<i>We don't need to be a national hero,</i>

648
00:58:18,962 --> 00:58:23,466
<i>a mythological figure,
or a character in a novel</i>

649
00:58:23,533 --> 00:58:27,604
<i>to work with others
toward change and progress.</i>

650
00:58:28,605 --> 00:58:30,974
<i>As long as it comes from the heart.</i>

651
00:58:31,040 --> 00:58:32,575
You have elevated blood pressure, sir.

652
00:58:32,642 --> 00:58:34,811
It's 150/100.

653
00:58:34,878 --> 00:58:36,312
But not that very high.

654
00:58:36,379 --> 00:58:38,848
Try to go for a run in the morning

655
00:58:38,915 --> 00:58:40,917
and do some exercise
to regulate your blood pressure.

656
00:58:42,886 --> 00:58:44,320
And here ma'am,

657
00:58:45,121 --> 00:58:48,625
give sir 50 milligrams once
a day, every morning, okay?

658
00:58:49,425 --> 00:58:51,528
And sir, I will ask you to stay away

659
00:58:51,594 --> 00:58:53,963
from fatty and oily foods, okay?

660
00:58:54,030 --> 00:58:55,365
See, I told you.

661
00:58:55,431 --> 00:58:56,900
You are not getting any younger,

662
00:58:56,966 --> 00:58:59,102
so you should eat
more fruits and vegetables, okay?

663
00:59:00,403 --> 00:59:01,804
-Thank you.
-Those are good.

664
00:59:02,839 --> 00:59:04,073
You two take care!

665
00:59:04,140 --> 00:59:05,041
All right.

666
00:59:05,108 --> 00:59:05,975
Let's go, Dad.

667
00:59:06,042 --> 00:59:07,977
See, I told you. Avoid eating…

668
00:59:08,044 --> 00:59:08,912
Is that all?

669
00:59:09,612 --> 00:59:11,381
<i>And what I know is,</i>

670
00:59:11,447 --> 00:59:13,049
<i>here in my heart,</i>

671
00:59:13,683 --> 00:59:18,187
<i>in creating change
in the story of my life,</i>

672
00:59:18,254 --> 00:59:20,123
<i>of my country,</i>

673
00:59:20,189 --> 00:59:22,258
<i>that I am not alone.</i>

674
00:59:25,762 --> 00:59:26,896
Ali?

675
00:59:30,667 --> 00:59:31,868
Mr. Torres?

676
00:59:39,075 --> 00:59:40,610
One moment, okay? I'll be back.

677
00:59:40,677 --> 00:59:42,145
All right, doctor.

678
00:59:42,211 --> 00:59:47,150
FREE MEDICAL SERVICES

679
01:00:26,756 --> 01:00:29,592
"Mystical figures"?

680
01:02:40,990 --> 01:02:42,325
<i>You're here now.</i>

681
01:02:59,776 --> 01:03:01,244
<i>I have found you.</i>

682
01:03:06,249 --> 01:03:07,750
<i>No more "goodbyes".</i>

683
01:03:09,452 --> 01:03:10,686
<i>No more "goodbyes".</i>

684
01:03:38,948 --> 01:03:42,018
A TRIBUTE TO YOU, DR. JOSE P. RIZAL.

685
01:03:42,084 --> 01:03:47,757
A TRIBUTE TO YOU,
DR. JOSE P. RIZAL. UNTIL THEN…

686
01:05:33,696 --> 01:05:35,731
THANK YOU VERY MUCH!

